ransomnote: There are conflicting reports regarding ransom demands. On May 5, 2015, it was reported that the assailants demands $100,000 for each prisoner, totaling $23,000,000 (Cross Map 05/05/2015). On October 9, 2015, it was reported that the assailants demanded $50,000 for each prisoner, totaling $14,000,000 (Christian Post, 10/19/2015). Later, reports noted that the assailants demanded $18,000,000 for the release of the hostage victims (San Francisco Chronicle, 2/22/2016). Finally, it was noted that less than $9,000,000 was paid for the release of the hostage victims (San Francisco Chronicle, 2/22/2016).
